parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause loss of power, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or navigating turns.
symptoms: The engine quits or dies without warning
the vehicle stalls when using the air conditioning
the vehicle stalls when turning corners at low speeds
the vehicle stalls when driving at cruise speeds
the vehicle requires shifting into neutral to restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the valve cover gasket can cause oil leaks, engine damage, and potentially lead to engine failure, which can result in costly repairs and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the valve cover area

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, decelerate, and potentially lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the vehicle lurches forward when stopped
the transmission fails to engage properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the starter and alternator can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: the alternator fails to charge the battery
the vehicle stalls or fails to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Axle failure can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
Defroster malfunction can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The defroster fails to clear the windshield

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cassette player failure is a minor issue that does not affect vehicle safety or performance.
symptoms: The cassette player fails to function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system can lead to unintended airbag deployment, which can cause injuries or fatalities, as well as failure to deploy in the event of a crash, which can increase the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: Sudden deployment of airbag without a crash
airbag warning light on the dashboard
repeated servicing of the airbag system without resolution
failure of the airbag to deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shimmy when the brakes are applied, leading to reduced stopping power and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shimmies or shakes when the brakes are applied
the brake pedal pulsates or vibrates
the brake pedal travels too far towards the floor
squeaking or grinding noises when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of multiple systems, including transmission, brakes, engine, and air conditioner, can lead to a loss of vehicle control, increased risk of accidents, and potentially leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: multiple warning lights or error messages on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A sudden battery failure can cause unexpected engine stall, loss of power, and potentially lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Spark plug failure can cause poor engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially lead to engine damage or failure.
An ignition switch short-circuit can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to unexpected loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
